Game UI Sketch Description
Main Rectangular Frame：
A prominent rectangular box is centered in the UI. In its top-left corner, there is a small triangle pointing inward or outward, likely serving as a decorative element, an icon placeholder, or a button indicator.
Right Side – Vertical Line with Triangle
Along the right side of the rectangle, a vertical straight line extends. 
Attached to this line (possibly at its midpoint or top end) is a small triangle. This might represent a slider track, a scrollbar, or a draggable handle for adjusting a setting like volume or brightness.
Bottom Side – Horizontal Line with Triangle
Below the rectangle, a horizontal line runs parallel to the bottom edge. A small triangle sits on this line,
likely indicating another slider or interactive control, possibly for horizontal adjustments such as time, progress, or value selection.
Bottom-Right Corner – Small Circle
At the bottom-right corner of the rectangle, there is a small circle. This could function as a confirm button, a settings icon, a resize handle, or a status indicator (e.g., ready, active, or unlocked).
